<!-- awf:section workflow -->
## Workflow

{{ if .skills.brainstorming }}Canonical chain for non-trivial work:

```
brainstorming → ADR (if warranted) → plan (if warranted) → resync (when both) → implementation → review → retrospective
```

Brainstorming is the hard prerequisite. An **ADR** is warranted by *load-bearing-ness* (a design decision the project must remember); when warranted it is written **and reviewed to a settled state before planning**, because the plan is execution detail derived from the decision. **Planning** is warranted by *complexity* (multi-commit, interdependent steps). Many tasks need neither, and the ADR↔plan relationship is many-to-one — one plan links zero or more ADRs. Each written artifact gets a fresh-context review (`{{ .prefix }}-reviewing-adr`, `{{ .prefix }}-reviewing-plan`); when both an ADR and a plan exist, a plan↔ADR **resync** reconciles them before implementation, looping until they converge. `{{ .prefix }}-reviewing-impl` is the terminal review, after which `{{ .prefix }}-retrospective` closes the feedback loop by promoting recurring findings toward deterministic checks.

**Chain skills** (invoke in order): `{{ .prefix }}-brainstorming`, `{{ .prefix }}-proposing-adr`, `{{ .prefix }}-reviewing-adr`, `{{ .prefix }}-writing-plans`, `{{ .prefix }}-reviewing-plan`, `{{ .prefix }}-reviewing-plan-resync`, `{{ .prefix }}-executing-plans` / `{{ .prefix }}-subagent-driven-development`, `{{ .prefix }}-reviewing-impl`, `{{ .prefix }}-retrospective`.{{ with .taskSkills }} **Task skills** (as needed): {{ . }}.{{ end }}

